items.sentence: I don't think anybody really wants to do that.
I don't think I have enough energy to do that.
I don't think that you should do that anymore.
I don't think that I really needed to do that.
I don't think that I had to do that yesterday.
I don't think that I could've done that alone.
I don't think that I could ever do that again.
You know Tom doesn't often do that, don't you?
You didn't know Tom couldn't do that, did you?
You and I both know that Tom needs to do that.
